                <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/> <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ule vindica te qui tibi male f<supplied reason="lost">aciet</supplied> qui <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><supplied reason="lost">v</supplied>indica te et si <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan> Statius tibi nocuit ab eo vind<supplied reason="lost">ica te <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></supplied> <lb n="3"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><supplied reason="lost" cert="low"> persequa</supplied>ris eum ut male contabescat usque dum morie<supplied reason="lost">t</supplied>ur <lb n="4"/>cumque alis et si Pollio conscius est et illum persequaris <lb n="5"/>ni <note>sic</note> annum ducat
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Eigenartige Form des Fluches, der an eine Gottheit gerichtet ist. Identifikation des Verfluchenden mit der Gottheit. (B): Morracchini-Mazel: weniger Ergänzungen, weniger und teilweise anders gelesen als Solin. Die Tafel ist in 3 Teile zerbrochen.</p>
